        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:20PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Baxterville, or 9 miles west of Purvis, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Purvis, Baxterville, and Pine Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
